rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Party
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A party represent: 1. a legal person having duties and rights as part of agreements. 2. a person known by an organisation (not necessarily providing its real name)

rdf:Description.dc:description: A field to allow to know who to contact to get more rights.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: International Standard Book Number, from 2007, unhyphenated (13 digits starting 978 or 9791–9799)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISBN13

rdf:Description.dc:description: A field to allow the author of the digital policy - if available this person may be eventually be contacted to obtain infomation about the license.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A unique number assigned to a bibliographic item by OCLC
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: OCLCNumber
GTIN13
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: GS1 Global Trade Item Number, formerly known as EAN article number (13 digits)

rdf:Description.dc:description: A field to allow to know who to contact to get more rights.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A Permission allows a particular Action to be executed on a related Asset, e.g. “play the audio file abc.mp3”. A Constraint like “at most 10 times” might be added to specify the Permission more precisely. The Party that grants this Permission is linked to it with the Role assigner, the Party that is granted the Permission is linked to it with the Role assignee, e.g. “assigner VirtualMusicShop grants the Permission to assignee Alice”. Additionally, a Permission MAY be linked to Duty entities.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Permission

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
An ODRL policy representing an agreement or a potential agreement.
Policy is the central entity that holds an ODRL policy together. In its encoded form, e.g. in an XML document, it makes the policy addressable from the outside word via its uid attribute. Policy can refer to Permissions and Prohibitions.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Policy

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
A digital right is the equivalent of a passport with visas. It defines what a user is allowed to do with one asset
A provable function of a an asset_descriptor use_context that tells you whether it is allowed to be in a state.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Right

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An ISBN-13 assigned by a co-publisher. The ‘main’ ISBN sent with ID type code 03 and/or 15 should always be the ISBN that is used for ordering from the supplier identified in Supply Detail. However, ISBN rules allow a co-published title to carry more than one ISBN. The co-publisher should be identified in an instance of the <Publisher> composite, with the applicable <PublishingRole> code
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CoPublisherSISBN13

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SPECIFY THE SEMANTIC OF PROHITION permit = default_everything_allowed-prohibition+permission prohib = default_nothing_allowed+permission-prohibition invalid = default_nothing_allowed+permission

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: JPMagazineID
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Japanese magazine identifier, similar in scope to ISSN but identifying a specific issue of a serial publication. Five digits to identify the periodical, plus a hyphen and two digits to identify the issue
Id who has the form of a URI
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: URI

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Prohibition entity is used in the same way as Permission, with the two differences that it does not refer to Duties and (obviously) that it forbids the Action, e.g. “Alice is forbidden to use abc.mp3 commercially”.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Prohibition
LegalDepositNumber
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The number assigned to a publication as part of a national legal deposit process

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Id
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Identifier for an asset.

Similar to Permissions, a Duty states that a certain Action MAY be executed by the Party with the Role assignee for the Permission to be valid, e.g. “Alice must pay 5 EUR in order to get the Permission to play abc.mp3″.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Duty

rdf:Description.dc:description: A field to allow to know who has been issuing the license and what what rights this person has.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Actionable ISBN, in fact a special DOI incorporating the ISBN-13 within the DOI syntax. Begins ‘10.978.’ or ‘10.979.’ and includes a / character between the registrant element (publisher prefix) and publication element of the ISBN, eg 10.978.000/1234567. Note the ISBN-A should always be accompanied by the ISBN itself, using codes 03 and/or 15
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISBNA

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Uniform Resource Name: note that in trade applications an ISBN must be sent as a GTIN-13 and, where required, as an ISBN-13 – it should not be sent as a URN
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: URN
GTIN14
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: GS1 Global Trade Item Number (14 digits)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: FreePermission
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Permission provided without duty requirement (useful for definition of rights)
They are assumed necessarily as odrl_Party as they have normally to give their rights at some point if they are contributors.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Asset
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
An asset in ODRL is any object referred by a policy.
In the copyrighthub these asset generally represent the intellectual work and metadata associated to particular instances of the work should not be included as metadata of the asset unless they are considered to be characteristic of the asset.
E-publication identifier controlled by JPOIID’s Committee for Research and Management of Electronic Publishing Codes
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: JPECode

rdf:Description.dc:description: A field to allow to know who to contact to get more rights.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Constraint
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Changes - added leftOperandProperty to give formal semantic linking original usecase / asset with the property checked - added leftOperandPropertyPath instead of a leftOperantProperty a properyt path may be used for instance "owner/position/country" - unit usage is discouraged as they should be specified by left operand property
UPC product number (12 digits)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: UPC

rdf:Description.dc:description: Optional expiry date of the policy. The policy is not considered valid after this date.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: International Standard Book Number, pre-2007, unhyphenated (10 characters) – now DEPRECATED in ONIX for Books, except where providing historical information for compatibility with legacy systems. It should only be used in relation to products published before 2007 – when ISBN-13 superseded it – and should never be used as the ONLY identifier (it should always be accompanied by the correct GTIN-13 / ISBN-13)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISBN10

rdf:Description.dc:description: A field to allow to know which server to contact to get more rights.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rule
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
Permission, Prohibition and Duty are Rules.
In order for "function" to complete "action" and to obtain "relation", function must satisfay constaint ?

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISMN10
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: International Standard Music Number (M plus nine digits). Pre-2008 – now DEPRECATED in ONIX for Books, except where providing historical information for compatibility with legacy systems. It should only be used in relation to products published before 2008 – when ISMN-13 superseded it – and should never be used as the ONLY identifier (it should always be accompanied by the correct ISMN-13)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISMN13
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: International Standard Music Number, from 2008 (13-digit number starting 9790)

Used only with comic books and other products which use the UPC extension to identify individual issues or products. Do not use where the UPC12 itself identifies the specific product, irrespective of any 5-digit extension – use code 04 instead
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: UPC125
DOI
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Digital Object Identifier (variable length and character set)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LCCN
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Library of Congress Control Number (12 characters, alphanumeric)
Authors are distinguished of contributors.
Unique number assigned by the Chinese Online Library Cataloging Center (see http://olcc.nlc.gov.cn)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: OLCCNumber
